(
<figureCitation id="98F21AC48EF4FF7A48905250FEAAFA64" box="[160,271,1404,1428]" captionStart="PLATE 50" captionStartId="188.[151,233,1920,1943]" captionTargetBox="[203,1404,212,1884]" captionTargetId="figure-105@188.[151,1436,195,1898]" captionText="PLATE 50. A–C. Chelae, holotypes. D–F. Male genitalia. 147. A. Anteon wushense (from Olmi 1991). B. A. xuexini (from Xu et al. 2001a). C. A. yangi (from Xu et al. 1998). D. A. yasiri, holotype (from Olmi 1998e). E. A. yasumatsui from China. F. A. yuani, holotype (from Xu et al. 1998). Scale bar 0.34 mm for A, 0.19 mm for B, 0.12 mm for C, 0.13 mm for D, 0.18 mm for E and 0.22 mm for F." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5278546" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5278546/files/figure.png" pageId="186" pageNumber="187">Plate 50A</figureCitation>
